snippet.textDisplay:
I think it's hard to accept good things that happen when we are so hard on ourselves. Often we are our own harshest critics and our own worst bullies. I once thought that if I put myself down all the time, then the people who also thought badly of me wouldn't be able to hurt me. I was wrong. Now I find it hard to even look at myself in the mirror and say one nice thing without breaking down. It's easy for me to build others up, but when it comes to myself all I do is see the things I fail at.



Everyone has something they are good at, even if it's just listening to a friend when they need to talk. I find it hard to think well of myself, to accept compliments. But when I see it in other people, I can recognize that in myself. I can rarely accept that a good thing has happened because I don't feel like I deserve anything good, ever.


I'm so proud to see how far you've come, Ethan. You've grown up and found your voice, the person who you are is shining through more and more each day. We love you. When I see you collab with other people the room seems just a bit brighter when you are there. A million might be just a number, but it's also people. You've made a mark on the internet and the world, one person at a time. Thank you for sharing a smile, a laugh, and even tears with us. I look forward to even more. :)
